parameters:
\SE[4]This is outside the village, you know. \!\SE[3]...I wonder
if it's not a good idea to go out alone.

\SE[4]This is outside the village, you know. \!\SE[3]...I wonder
if it's not a good idea to go out alone.
\SE[1]Ah... It's Aisha. \!Should I try calling out to her...?\!

\SE[2] (She's working so hard... I wonder if it would be
bothersome to interrupt. \SE[45] I'm just not very good at
this...)

\SE[3]Hmm... everyone seems busy. I wonder what I should do
today...
Huh, Vita. What are you doing in a place like this?

\SE[10]What's wrong...? You forgot your bento, right? \SE[4]I
came to deliver it to you.

Oh... I'm sorry! I must have been half asleep and forgotten!
Thank you! My daughter!
\SE[0]Yes. It's good to work hard. Father.
\SE[2]I wonder if Aisha is working somewhere...?

I'm not exactly a great father. I need to make my family feel
even a little bit of happiness...

Washing pebbles one by one... It's not really my thing... but I
do get paid for it...

Hey there, miss. Your work is delicate, so I mustn't disturb you,
okay?

It seems that following the manual's instructions is important...
It seems like it will be difficult to get all the villagers to
thoroughly understand it...

Ah... it's just a chore, but it feels good to see the stones
getting cleaner and cleaner...

I wonder what I should use the money for... Maybe I'll go to the
city... and spend it at a naughty shop...

Everyone seems to be closing their shops and polishing stones.
I'm doing the same too...

I'm keeping watch so they don't slack off. \!... It seems like
everyone in this village is serious.

I heard a rumor that this stone can completely transform into a
different substance with changes in temperature.
NPC Name A Little More Knowledgeable Villager

......Ah, yeah, that's right. I don't really know the details. I
just wanted to show off that I knew something.

There's a limited amount of space by the river, so it's become a
competition. Starting tomorrow, we're going to have a rotation
system.

My skin gets rough from doing water work. I need to buy high-
quality lotion with the money I received... But somehow, it feels
like such a waste.
It seems like they're very focused...

They say it's better to polish stones and earn money to buy food
than to work in the fields. Don't you think we're being deceived?
Us...

We will be closed for a while because we are polishing the
stones! \.......It seems that the tool shop is not open.

We store the finished refined stones there. No one except
authorized personnel is allowed to enter, okay?

For a while, lunchtime will be closed. We will be open as usual
in the evening. ... is written.

After cleaning the stones, they heat them with fire and then cool
them in the river. I wonder what the meaning of doing such a
thing is.

My wife kicked me out, saying Go polish stones instead of running
an unprofitable tavern! And yet she tells me to work on nights
when I can earn money... Ugh.

Aisha has a Sable Noir that she keeps... It seems a little lonely
because there is no one to play with... Should I pet it?
Cats seem to have no interest in stone polishing at all.

If there's any trouble, please let me know. At that time, I will
fight as a soldier.
When it's lunchtime, I'll help too. Let's do it together, Vita.

\SE[6]Hmm... I think I'll pass on this one... \SE[9]I'm not good
with delicate tasks, and I have strong strength, so I might end
up breaking the stones and getting in everyone's way...

Y-You're right, Vita's grip strength is amazing... W-Well then,
I'll leave the hunting to you again. This time, I want to eat
deer meat!

Everyone is working so hard... I should make some snacks to bring
in the afternoon...

What should I do with the money I received... Maybe I'll buy some
nice clothes and start 'Yuriseen' to try my hand at
matchmaking...
